div.p: A Python application that automatically updates a Google Keeps note containing a list of games, sorted by release date, to keep track of upcoming games that will be released. The main purpose of this app is to stop manually updating Google Keep note regarding upcoming games as performing that activity automatically is preferred.

ul.li: User enters name of Video Game through GUI and clicks Add (or press enter)
The app should read Google Keep to get a list of game titles and determine whether the game being added already exists
If the app exists, inform the user it's already on the list
Else add it to the game list and continue:
Scrape IGDB database for the inputted game.
Save the release date of the game and update the game list.
Generate a list of games, sorted based on release date (released games being at the top while TBD dates are at the bottom)
Write list to Google Keeps note concerning Games Radar, updating all changed entries.
Automatically update release date for all games every month
